34 Well I discerned in them the blond head;
35 but in the face the eye was lost,
36 as virtue that becomes too confused.

43 And Sordello also: “Now let us descend indeed
44 among the great shadows, and we will speak to them;
45 it will be pleasing to them to see us enough.”

52 He became visible to me, and I to him;
53 gentle Nin, judge, how much it pleased me
