query.prompt:
Please translate each line literally into English.

118 Fui chiamato Currado Malaspina;
119 non son l’antico, ma di lui discesi;
120 a’ miei portai l’amor che qui raffina».

query.result:
118 I was called Currado Malaspina;
119 I am not the ancient one, but from him I descended;
120 to my people I carried the love that here refines.

121 “Oh!” said I to him, “through your lands 122 never have I been; but where he dwells 123 throughout Europe that they are not manifest?
124 The fame that your house honors, 125 cries the lords and cries the countryside, 126 so that knows he who has not yet been there;
127 and I swear to you, if I go above, 128 that your honored people will not be tarnished 129 by the worth of the purse and of the sword.”
